   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <hazardstatement type="danger" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">HAZARD OF ELECTRIC SHOCK, EXPLOSION, OR ARC FLASH</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Always repack cabinets to their original delivered packing
condition. Moisture inside cabinets can create hazardous short circuits. </howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <hazardstatement type="notice" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">Damaged Batteries</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Never store batteries more than 6 months. If the batteries
are de-energized for a long period of time, the batteries must be
charged for 24 hours at least once every month.</howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">If vacuum
sealed aluminium foil is used and the vacuum is lost and can’t
be resealed, the cabinet is no longer protected from moisture.</note>
         <p class="- topic/p ">If systems or batteries needs to be stored a short time after
delivery but before installation, the systems should be stored in
the transportation crate with the sealed inner packing intact.</p>
